The article is a proclamation issued by President Donald Trump on March 24, 2020, in celebration of Greek Independence Day. The proclamation highlights the historical and cultural ties between the United States and Greece, emphasizing the shared values of freedom and democracy. It mentions the support of Americans for Greek independence in the past and the strengthening of the defense and security partnership between the two countries. The proclamation also acknowledges the contributions of Greek-Americans and reaffirms the commitment to deepening the relationship between the two nations. President Trump declares March 25, 2020, as Greek Independence Day and calls upon the people of the United States to observe the day with appropriate ceremonies and activities.